commits.commitMessage:
Fix session cleanup bug

The function swi_mangoh_data_router_removeAllUpdateHandlersForSession
was iterating over database items incorrectly which meant that the
code was executing as though there was nothing to clean up when there
was data to clean and executing as though there was something to
clean up when there was nothing.  In the latter case, this caused an
assert in the data router.  This bug was also masking another bug in
the ListRemoveGeneral() helper function.  In addition, the severity of
the "session not found" messages has been incresed to error because
reads/writes of values should never occur without a session.

Resolves: MANGOH-4
Change-Id: If50b3ef1b8936e6ee81ee5de01ef9a5fd341da10
commits.subject: Fix session cleanup bug

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

I believe this change is incompatible with Legato 16.01.2 and thus will not build with the mangoh.xml manifest.  For that reason, I would prefer to see this pushed to refs/heads/Legato_16.04.  I can't actually figure out whether it is possible to view which branch this change is proposed for in gerrit.  Is there a way to do this?

Patch Set 1:

The "reply" dialog was covering the branch specification, so disregard my previous comment about not being able to tell which branch this was proposed for.

Patch Set 1:

I don't understand why you guys are saying this is not compatible with versions of Legato prior to 16.04.  

Prior to 16.04, native C types were allowed in .api files, so you could use float, double, or whatever you wanted.  This usage was discouraged in the docs, but not prevented in any way.

With 16.04, the type checking has been improved.  double is now a built-in type, but float is not.
